<p>HUMAN RIGHTS COUNCIL 
Fourth session 
Agenda item 2 
</p>
<p><b>IMPLEMENTATION OF GENERAL ASSEMBLY RESOLUTION 60/251  
OF 15 MARCH 2006 ENTITLED &#8220;HUMAN RIGHTS COUNCIL&#8221; 
</b></p>
<p><b>Report of the United Nations High Commissioner for Human Rights 
on the human rights situation and the activities of her Office,  
                         including technical cooperation, in Nepal 
</b></p>
<p><b>Addendum 
</b></p>
<p><b>VISIT OF THE HIGH COMMISSIONER FOR HUMAN RIGHTS TO NEPAL 
</b></p>
<p><b>Corrigendum 
</b></p>
<p><b>Annex 
</b><i>Paragraph 1 
</i></p>
<p> For the existing text <i>substitute</i> 
</p>
<p>1. The High Commissioner visited Nepal from 19 to 24 January 2007 to review the  
work of her field office in Nepal and to highlight the centrality of human rights in the peace 
process - at this critical juncture - as well as to call attention on a number of long-standing 
discrimination issues which have come to the fore since the April ceasefire and recently led to 
demonstrations, to lethal confrontations with the police, and to communal violence. 
</p>
<p><i>Paragraph 3 
</i></p>
<p> The last sentence <i>should read 
</i></p>
<p> OHCHR is committed to providing appropriate assistance to civil society and the 
authorities to help determine the best course of action with regard to transitional justice. 
</p>
